The unit test workflow is very simple. 

1. Mock the dependencies and their return value for the method/function you want to test. Make an isolated environment for it. The principle is the unit tests shouldn&#39;t depend on any external service, e.g. send a real HTTP request, query the real database, access the real file system.

2. Execute the method/function you want to test, test each branch(`if...else`, `switch...case`), statements, functions, and lines. They are the summary of the coverage report.

3. Assert(`expect`) the result and if the methods/functions on which the method/function being tested depends are to be called. Why? Because we should make sure the code execute as we expect

Test each method/function as the above workflow in each software arch layer. 

The software arch layer means, for example, data access layer, model layer,  service layer, controller/router layer

Here is the correct unit test:

`index.ts`:

```typescript
